<HEADLINE>
SILVERBULLETDAY TO RUN IN BELMONT, BAFFERT SAYS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY MOSS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
The past two years, trainer Bob Baffert has had Triple Crown bids
spoiled in the Belmont Stakes. 
<TEXT>
<P>
   This year, he hopes to play the spoiler. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Baffert said yesterday that his 3-year-old filly Silverbulletday
will run against males for the first time in the June 5 Belmont.
There she will face Kentucky Derby and Preakness winner
Charismatic, who stands to collect a $5 million Visa Triple Crown
bonus should he also win the Belmont. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Silverbulletday has scored eight consecutive victories against
females, most by decisive margins. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``She's a pure athlete,'' owner Mike Pegram said of
Silverbulletday. ``You're always concerned going a mile-and-a-half,
but good athletes have ways of doing things they ain't supposed to
do and, hopefully, that's what she'll do.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   On Tuesday, Silverbulletday worked a scorching six furlongs in 1
minute, 10 4/5 seconds at Churchill Downs. The way she behaved
after that workout clinched the deal, Baffert says. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``We got her out, and she was just full of herself,'' Baffert
said. ``That's a good sign. It just goes to show that she's fit,
but she has the lung capacity for it. You cannot train a horse to
run a mile and a half at the top level. They either can do it or
they can't do it, and I think she's got the lung capacity.` &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Jerry Bailey is scheduled to ride Silverbulletday in the
Belmont. Her regular rider, Gary Stevens, is scheduled to leave the
United States at the end of this month to begin riding in England. &QL; 
Breeders' Cup outlook &QL; 
A Breeders' Cup in Texas won't be possible until at least 2003. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Breeders' Cup president D.G. Van Clief announced yesterday that
the 2000 races will return to Churchill Downs for the fifth time.
Santa Anita had originally been chosen as next year's host, but had
to back out because of remodeling plans. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   At the same time, the Breeders' Cup board of directors
unofficially indicated a preference for New York's Belmont Park in
2001, and Santa Anita in 2002. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Van Clief said new sites for the Breeders' Cup will be
considered for 2003. Lone Star Park and Houston's Sam Houston Race
Park have expressed an interest in holding the event. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   This year's Breeders' Cup is scheduled for Nov. 6 at Gulfstream
Park in Hallandale, Fla. &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
