<P>
   COXNET ENTERTAINMENT 0527 -- Can a rock band be blamed for the
deadly actions of fervent fans? Of course. The finger-pointing has
happened time and again. But does that mean there's a provable
cause-and-effect relationship when a young fan goes over the edge?
(Riemenschneider, Austin American-Statesman) Art includes 4-column
color illustration of a smoking gun. The smoke from the gun forms a
guitar.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   ON VIDEO _ Now that ``Episode I _ The Phantom Menace'' is out in
the theaters, this might be a good time to contemplate some of the
sources that fired George Lucas' imagination and helped form the
``Star Wars'' mythos. (Ringel-Gillespie, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes 1-column color photo of
columnist.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO REVIEWS _ ``Saving Private Ryan,'' a tale of a squadron of
soldiers sent behind enemy lines to rescue one soldier, achieves
cumulative power through many indelible moments. Also, ``Theory of
Flight,'' ``Gloria,'' and ``Alice in Wonderland.'' (Staff, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes 18-pica color photo from
``Saving Private Ryan.''
</P>
<P>
   CD REVIEWS _ Tim McGraw has always been a refreshing exclamation
point in the often flat-line world of country music. But McGraw's
new album marks a disappointing change. While technically
proficient, it's somewhat bland _ like a mess of greens without the
salt pork. Also, C Note, Moby and Mary Chapin Carpenter. (Staff,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes 1-column color photo of
Tim McGraw.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE NEWS AND REVIEWS/FROM ATLANTA
</P>
<P>
   STARWARS-PARODY _ Video parodies of the Star War series abound
on the Internet. The most well-known is Troops, which plays like an
episode of ``Cops'' starring Imperial Storm Troopers on the beat on
Tattoine. One, ``Trooper Clerks,'' was made this year by a bunch of
folks who work in advertising in Atlanta. It's a scene-by-scene
reshoot of the trailer for ``Clerks,'' with storm troopers behind
the counter. ``Phantom Menace'' has its share of spoofs too,
including ``south park'' themed ones. And then there's the you
might be a Jedi redneck list ..... Photos of Jeff Allen of Auburn
and friends in trooper costumes from Trooper Clerks. (Lee, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 16. PARODYWEBSITES _ Short list of Web sites
where you can find ``Star Wars'' humor. (Lee, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 3.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-HILL _ Movie Review. ``Notting Hill.'' Romantic comedy
with Julia Roberts and Hugh Grant.(Murray, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-THREE _ Review of ``Three Seasons,'' the Sundance
Festival winner from Tony Bui, about modern-day Vietnam. Grade: B.
(Ringel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12
</P>
