<P>
   REVIEW-NOTTING _ Review of ``Notting Hill.'' A hapless London
bookstore owner finds his life disrupted when a famous movie star
enters his store and shoplifts his heart. With Julia Roberts, Hugh
Grant. (Macor, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-FLOOR _ Review of ``The Thirteenth Floor.'' A man is
suspected of killing his boss. He must enter a virtual world in
search of the truth. With Craig Bierko, Gretchen Mol, Vincent
D'Onofrio. (Garcia, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ Weekly movie column. (Garcia, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-NOTES _ Limited runs and film notes. (Garcia, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-HIDEOUS _ Review of ``Hideous Kinky.'' A young British
hippie takes her two young daughters with her on a journey of
spiritual discovery through Morocco in the 1960s. Little adventures
ensue, including the big one called love. Stars Kate Winslet in her
first post-''Titanic'' role. (Macor, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-SEASONS _ Review of ``Three Seasons.'' Three desperate,
disparate story lines intersect in Vietnam; in one, a shattered vet
(Harvey Keitel) searches for his long-lost daughter. Grand Jury
Prize and Audience Award winner at this year's Sundance. (Macor,
Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-METROLAND _ Review of ``Metroland.'' Late '60s period
piece about two friends who abandon suburban London in favor of
bohemian global adventures. (Seaborn, Austin American-Statesman).
