   WITH: REVIEW WHOLE WOMAN -- When Germaine Greer's swaggering
call for sexual liberation, ``The Female Eunuch,'' appeared in
1970, it created a sensation. Now, some 30 years later, Ms. Greer
has written a sequel of sorts. It's a book that is as sour as
``Eunuch'' was exuberant. (Kakutan, N.Y. Times News Service) Art
includes 6-pica color photo of book jacket.
