<P>
   CHINA-RENO (Washington) _ Attorney General Janet Reno defends
the Justice Department's handling of suspected espionage in the
nation's atomic laboratories and says she will not resign. By JOHN
C. HENRY.
</P>
<P>
   TRANSPORTATION-MONEY (Washington) _ New York and California
would lose transit funding in cutbacks approved by the Senate
Appropriations Committee. New York would lose $200 million and
California, $117 million, if the overall $12 billion measure
passes. Rep. John Sweeney, R-N.Y., and Sen. Dianne Feinstein,
D-Calif., vow to fight the cuts. By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN.
</P>
<P>
   ABORTION-CONSENT (Washington) _ A House panel examines a
proposal that would outlaw taking minors across state lines to
circumvent laws requiring parents to be notified before their
daughters can get an abortion. By STEVE LASH.
</P>
