   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-VACATION (Yulee, Fla.) _ As they frolic on a secluded
Florida plantation, President Clinton and Hillary Rodham Clinton
keep in touch with the real world, especially what's ahead for the
first lady as she explores running for a Senate seat in New York.
By BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   SHUTTLE-STATION (Cape Canaveral, Fla.) _ The Discovery and its
international crew hurtle toward a meeting with the international
space station, carrying supplies that include drinking water and
laptop computers. By MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
   SHIP-COCAINE (Orange, Texas) _ The U.S. Customs Service will
auction off the Cannes, a tanker it seized in January in the Texas'
largest cocaine bust. The Panamanian-flag bulk freighter is the
largest vessel seized by Customs since 1990. By JENALIA MORENO.
</P>
