</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-JEWISH-VOTE (Washington)_ If First Lady Hillary Rodham
Clinton runs for a Senate seat from New York, she will need the
help of a key constituency in the state: Jewish voters. She got in
hot water last year with many Jews by advocating a Palestinian
state. But her backers say Jewish public opinion on that subject is
divided, and that the Jewish vote will be swayed more by her stands
on such issues as education, health care and Social Security. By
DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
