   KOSOVO-ARMY (Undated) _ The Yugoslav army's purge of Kosovo this
spring was designed by officers who were determined not to repeat
the mistakes made by Serbia's Interior Ministry security forces in
last summer's failed attempt to crush the rebels of the Kosovo
Liberation Army, according to NATO officials. And the officials now
acknowledge that they missed signs that the Yugoslav army was
preparing a much more extensive operation in Kosovo that would move
well beyond attacking KLA strongolds to cities and towns that had
no direct ties to the rebels. By John Kifner and Michel R. Gordon.
</P>
