of the surface of Mars reveals an impact basin deep enough to
swallow Mount Everest and surprising slopes in Valles Marineris.
The map, constructed with data from the Mars Global Surveyor and
released Thursday afternoon by NASA, will influence scientific
understanding of the red planet for years. By Warren E. Leary.
</P>
