and New Orleans: A French Impressionist in America'' through Aug.
29. In addition to works created in New Orleans during Degas' visit
with relatives in 1872, the exhibition includes paintings done by
Degas of relatives visting France prior to his U.S. visit, and
examples of his most recognized subjects, such as opera and racing
scenes, completed after his return to Paris. 1-800-409-9959.
</P>
