<P>
   ADAM-YAHOO _ Adam.com has forged a deal with Yahoo that Adam's
CEO calls the most significant move yet in the company's Internet
campaign. The agreement puts Adam content and Adam links on Yahoo's
new healthcare portal. (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ENCOMPASS _ATLANTA _Yahoo! said it is buying Encompass
Technologies, an Atlanta company, for $130 million. (Clothier,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COKE-DISCRIMINATION _ Plaintiffs in the racial discrimination
lawsuit against Atlanta-based Coca-Cola Co. plan are expected to
file motions today challenging Chairman M. Douglas Ivester's plans
to hold meetings with small groups of black employees to discuss
diversity issues. Plaintiffs lawyers also plan to complain that the
company is sending out letters to employees without a court-ordered
disclaimer that says: ``The foregoing represents Coca-Cola's
opinion of this olawsuit. It is unlawful for Coca-Cola to retaliate
against employees who choose to participate in this case. (Unger,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   CARSALES-HAULERS _ Last summer, it was the United Auto Workers
strike at General Motors Corp. parts plants that disrupted car
sales. This summer, it may be the Teamsters Union who throw car
sales into a skid. If the Teamsters strike _ and they have
threatened to do so at the end of Memorial Day _ the work stoppage
will hurt all the major automakers and many of their dealers, and
threaten what is shaping up to be a record year for vehicle sales.
(Ritzler, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
