   SCHOOL-DELAY (Los Angeles) _ Two San Fernando Valley primary
centers that L.A. Unified officials pledged would open by September
despite the discovery of toxic problems characterized as minor now
will not open as scheduled because district planners failed to get
proper review of the architectural plans. By Terri Hardy. (Will
move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LAPD-RACISM (Los Angeles) _ Police Chief Bernard Parks gave an
impassioned speech Thursday on racism, as a result of protests over
the police shooting of a homeless woman. Parks said the LAPD cannot
be blamed for 200 years of racism and the race issue should not
fall on the shoulders of officers. By Rick Orlov. (Will move in the
``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-SUMMER (Los Angeles) _ Fire up those barbecues! The
unofficial start of summer, Memorial Day weekend, approaches with
promise of cool, cloudy weather, but that isn't deterring folks
from filling campground reservations. The auto club and LAX predict
heavy travel. By Steve Carney. (Will move in the ``n'' California
news file.)
