<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, MAY 28
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-KOSOVO-NATO-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 25)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 25,
about NATO's approval of a 50,000-member peacekeeping force for
Kosovo and its approval of a plan to search ships that may be
carrying fuel to Yugoslavia included an erroneous reference from
NATO to Malta's intended role. Malta has indeed agreed to take part
in the embargo and has instructed Maltese-registered ships to stay
clear of the area.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-UNIVERSE-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 25)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 25,
about a newly calculated rate of expansion of the universe referred
incorrectly in some editions to the speed at which a galaxy appears
to be flying away from Earth. It is 70 kilometers per second per
megaparsec _ that is, 160,000 miles per hour faster for every 3.26
million light-years of distance from Earth, not for every 3.26
light-years.
</P>
<P>
   BC-WAIKIKI-BEACHBOY-NYT (moved on Thursday, May 13)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, May 13,
about the funeral of Charles Lambert, a Waikiki beach boy and later
convention manager in Honolulu, referred incorrectly to his
ancestry. He was not a descendant of Queen Liliuokalani, the
Hawaiian Islands' last monarch; she had no children.
</P>
