<P>
   (NYT19) ATLANTA -- May 27, 1999 -- BOSNIA-BABY-COX, 5-27 -- Azra
Beso recovers from cardiac surgery after a team of nine doctors
switched the baby's main heart arteries, which were transposed at
birth. Azra's arrival in Atlanta last month was unexpected. She was
aboard a Delta Air Lines flight from Vienna, Austria, to Detroit
for scheduled heart surgery there when her breathing became labored
halfway across the Atlantic Ocean. (Joey Ivansco/Cox News Service)
