<P>
   (NYT18) KYOTO, Japan -- May 27, 1999 -- JAPAN-GENJI, 5-27 --
Jakucho Setouchi, author of the best-selling translation of ``Tale
of Genji,'' at a temple where she is a Buddhist nun. Genji is an
unusual Japanese cultural icon and his latest chronicler is if
anything even more startling. ``When a man and a woman are in love,
the situation hasn't changed in the last thousand years,'' Ms.
Setouchi said cheerfully when commenting about the success of her
work. (Nicholas D. Kristof/New York Times Photo) LITE
