   (NYT15) NEW YORK -- May 27, 1999 -- MISSING-CHILDREN-FLOATER,
5-27 -- New York City school students march carrying portraits of
missing children in lower Manhattan on Thursday. Over 2,000
children marched to mark National Missing Children's Day which was
organized by the National Center for Missing and Exploited
Children. An additional focus of the event was to instruct the
children taking part in the march on simple rules for personal
safety. (Jack Manning/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) DENVER -- May 27, 1999 -- COLO-SCHOOL-SUIT, 5-27 --
Geoffrey Fieger, background, discusses the law suit that was filed
against the parents of Columbine High School killers Eric Harris
and Dylan Klebold during a news conference on Thursday. Fieger
filed the suit on behalf of Michael Shoels and his wife, the
parents of Isaiah Shoels who was one of 12 Columbine students
killed at the school on April 20. (Kevin Moloney/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
