   (NYT13) WASHINGTON -- May 27, 1999 -- CONGRESS-GUNS, 5-27 --
Vice President Al Gore hugs Byrl Phillips-Taylor during a gun
safety event on Capitol Hill on Thursday. Phillips-Taylor's son
Scott was killed eight years ago by a classmate with an assault
rifle. Rep. Grace Napolitano, D-Calif., looks on at right. (Shana
Raab/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) UNDATED -- May 27, 1999 -- APPETIZERS-FOOD-AZR, 5-27 --
Dips and chips will be forever with us. But it's time to get a new
appetizer life. Just in time for Memorial Day entertaining, a party
host should explore the world of Canapes, Hors D'Oeuvres and
Appetizers. This tray of canapes contains such delights as shrimp
stuffed with feta and dill, chile cheese puffs, artichoke nibbles
and mushroom phyllo triangles. (Sherrie Buzby/Arizona Republic
Photo)
</P>
