Carlos Fernandez Gonzalez, chief executive officer of Grupo Modelo,
the makers of Corona beer among other labels, in a corporate office
on Wednesday. In 10 years, Grupo Modelo has transformed Corona from
a once-obscure Mexican beer into a global brand whose recognition
approaches that of Coca-Cola or Marlboro cigarettes. (Keith
Dannemiller/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) OXNARD, Calif. -- May 27, 1999 -- CALIF-PICKERS-UNION-2,
5-27 -- Strawberry workers and their supporters wait outside the
local United Farmworkers Union office for news on the results of an
election on Thursday. Pickers for the nation's largest strawberry
grower voted overwhelmingly to unionize, but state labor officials
said early Thursday that it was too close to call which union would
represent the workers. (Monica Almeida/New York Times Photo) LITE
