<P>
   &QL; 
SMOKE-TRIBES (Phoenix) _ Former Navajo Tribal Chairman Albert Hale
has gotten 30 Indian nations around the country to sign on to a $1
billion lawsuit against tobacco companies. Hale expects to file the
suit next month. The suit is very similar to the state lawsuits
that led to billions in settlements.
</P>
<P>
   Tobacco use on Indian Reservations has skyrocketed in recent
years, and Hale says Native Americans should be accorded the same
rights to sue Big Tobacco as the states. By CHRIS MOESER. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
